						               													<description>We invite you to become an architect of legendary pyramids. To conquer fame and wealth, this will be the gift from Pharaoh. The board game Architects of Giza is a &amp;laquo;roll-and-write&amp;raquo; game, made for 2-4 players and the duration of play no longer than 20 minutes. One turn of the game consist a few rounds, each of them is separated into 2 stages. During the 1st stage players one by one are throwing the dice and writing the summary of numbers of selected dice into the cell of a pyramid. Depending on the quantity of selected dice player can write the summary only into the specific rows. Written numbers have value for the final score, but not only the quantity directly, but also the rows which are completed and pairs of the same numbers will bring additional points. During the 2 stage players have to decide their order for the next turn, because this is an important detail which can bring not only better choice, but also bonuses during the game and in the end as well. &amp;#10;To play Architects of Giza, you need: notepad with the game fields, 6 playing dice D6 and pencils for writing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
